Sentencas: Solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) are widely utilized for energy conversion applications, due to their remarkable electrochemical performance, economical and environmental points of view.
Titulo: A multiscale-architecture solid oxide fuel cell fabricated by electrophoretic deposition technique

Sentencas: In the present study, a multiscale-architecture SOFC, consisting of NiO-YSZ anode, NiO-YSZ anode functional layer (AFL), YSZ electrolyte, and bi-layered LSM/LSM-YSZ cathode is fabricated; where innovatively all the layers are deposited by environmentally-friendly electrophoretic deposition.
Titulo: A multiscale-architecture solid oxide fuel cell fabricated by electrophoretic deposition technique

Sentencas: Identifying and investigations on the structure and morphology of the samples are carried out by field emission scanning electron microscopy (FE-SEM), representing the high porosity of different layers.

Sentencas: Good peak power densities of 0.477 (with H2 fuel) and 0.420 W cm2 (with CH4 fuel) at open-circuit voltages (OCV) of 0.89 and 0.80 V are achieved at the operating temperature of 800 C. These lower OCVs than the theoretical OCV value, confirm the porous structure of the YSZ electrolyte.
